    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis PR fix the expert_ids padding value in moe_align_block_size kernel.\n* Current `moe_align_block_size` kernel padding expert_ids is 0. But this should be -1, because the downstream kernel expect invalid expert_ids to be -1, see https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/v0.16.0/vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/fused_moe.py#L431\n* Updated test cases in test_moe_align_block_size.py\n\n## Test Plan\n\n```\npytest -s -v tests/kernels/moe/test_moe_align_block_size.py\n```\n\n## Test Result\n\nUnit tests passed.\n\n## Accuracy Testing\n\n```\nvllm serve deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1-0528 \\\n    --tensor-parallel-size 8 \\\n    --max-num-seqs 8 \\\n    --trust-remote-code \\\n    --no-enable-prefix-caching\n\npython3 -m lm_eval --model local-completions \\\n  --model_args model=deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1-0528,base_url=http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/completions,num_concurrent=8 \\\n  --tasks gsm8k\n```\n\nMain:\n\n```\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9545|±  |0.0057|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9545|±  |0.0057|\n```\n\nPR:\n\n```\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9545|±  |0.0057|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9545|±  |0.0057|\n```\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
